I"f<h2 id="rules-of-the-pre-print">Rules of the Pre-Print</h2>

<p>A pre-print is the submitted version of a journal article. It can be updated as revisions are made, if the journal allows such updates.</p>

<h2 id="when-to-submit-a-pre-print">When to Submit a Pre-Print</h2>

<p>Submit a pre-print when you submit the article for consideration by a journal.</p>

<h2 id="where-to-submit-a-pre-print">Where to Submit a Pre-Print</h2>

<p>The ArXiv or the Engineering ArXiv.</p>

<h2 id="after-submitting-a-pre-print">After Submitting a Pre-Print</h2>

<p>Add it to the ARFC Zotero, the ARFC Website, and your CV.</p>
